Tesco is close to ditching the last of the private jets used by its top executives after an accounting scandal in its 95-year history .
Britain 's biggest grocer operated a multimillion-pound fleet of five aircraft for its bosses , but after a disastrous year new chief executive Dave Lewis admitted the planes gave the wrong image and put them up for sale .
Four have been sold and the final one , a Hawker 800 , will be gone by the end of next month .